# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## [Unreleased]

### 🚀 Features

- **PKCS#11 ObjectsStore**: Fix variable-shadowing bug in `upsert()` that silently no-op'd updates — stub objects with empty key bytes were never replaced with properly-fetched objects, causing `C_GetAttributeValue` to return `CKR_GENERAL_ERROR` for all public-key attributes.
- **PKCS#11 public key attributes**: Guard `CKA_MODULUS` / `CKA_PUBLIC_EXPONENT` attribute handlers with `is_rsa()` check; return `None` for non-RSA keys instead of propagating `CKR_GENERAL_ERROR`.
- **PKCS#11 EC point encoding**: Wrap `CKA_EC_POINT` bytes in a DER OCTET STRING per PKCS#11 v2.40 spec so OpenSSH/OpenSSL's `o2i_ECPublicKey` can parse them correctly.
- **PKCS#11 RSA/EC key bytes**: Fix `Pkcs11PublicKey` to store the inner key bytes extracted from SPKI's BIT STRING (`raw_bytes()`) rather than the full SPKI DER, so `RsaPublicKey::from_der` and `p256::PublicKey::from_sec1_bytes` succeed.
- **test_openssh.sh**: New shell integration test for the OpenSSH PKCS#11 provider; invokes `ssh-keygen -D` to enumerate RSA and EC P-256 public keys via the PKCS#11 library.
- **test_luks.sh**: New shell integration test for the LUKS disk-encryption PKCS#11 scenario (Rust unit tests + shell verification with `ckms locate`).
- **nix.sh**: Add `openssh` and `luks` test cases; export `WITH_OPENSSH=1`/`WITH_LUKS=1`; auto-select `non-fips` variant for both test types when not explicitly specified; disable `--pure` on macOS so system `ssh-keygen` is accessible.
- **shell.nix**: Add `pkgs.openssh` (Linux) when `WITH_OPENSSH=1` and `pkgs.opensc` (Linux) when `WITH_LUKS=1` so CI runners have the required tools.
- **test_all.yml**: Add `openssh` and `luks` to the CI test matrix (non-fips only; fips excluded because PKCS12KDF and EdDSA are not FIPS-approved).
- **CI fix**: Increase KMS server startup timeout in `test_openssh.sh` and `test_luks.sh` from 60 s to 120 s to give CI runners enough time to boot the server.
- **CI fix**: Start KMS in `test_openssh.sh` and `test_luks.sh` with an explicit generated `kms.toml` (`--config`) to avoid default-config startup hangs in CI runners.
- **CI fix**: Probe KMS readiness on `/` instead of `/kmip/2_1` in OpenSSH/LUKS scripts to avoid intermittent KMIP probe timeouts while the server is already listening.
- **Test stability**: Before OpenSSH/LUKS Rust unit tests, kill stale listeners on port 9998 to prevent `start_default_test_kms_server` failures (`Address already in use`).
- **CI fix**: Export `WITH_CURL=1` for `openssh`/`luks` nix test types and fail fast in `kms_wait_ready` if curl is missing, preventing silent readiness timeouts in pure nix-shell jobs.
- **CI fix**: Add `ui/.prettierignore` to exclude `pnpm-lock.yaml` from Prettier checks (Nix pnpm 9 rewrites the lock file format, then Prettier 3.8.1 rejects it).
- **CI fix**: Skip `test_db_postgresql_mtls_connection` in the regular psql CI test run (the `postgres-mtls` Docker service is not started there) to stop the `test_db_postgresql` substring filter from accidentally running the mTLS-only test.
- **CI fix**: In `test_luks.sh`, treat `pkcs11-tool` `C_FindObjectsInit`/`CKR_ARGUMENTS_BAD` as an OpenSC/provider compatibility path and fall back to `ckms locate` + Rust PKCS#11 enumeration checks instead of hard-failing on tool-specific listing output.
- **Docs**: Reintegrate PKCS#11 pages from `cli_documentation/docs/pkcs11` into main docs under `documentation/docs/integrations`, grouping database integrations in `integrations/databases`, disk encryption in `integrations/disk_encryption`, and adding an OpenSSH integration entry.
